        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 6:46PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 646 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Indian Land, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Indian Land, Waxhaw, Andrew Jackson State Park, Van Wyck, Carolina
Commons Shopping Center, and Community of Almond Glen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
